        <mxCell id="d7-detail-pane" value="Enigma I — Wehrmacht
[BROKEN / Operational 1930–1945]
[ Image Placeholder — 480 × 180 ]
Specifications:
Rotors:     3 (from set I–V)
Reflector:  UKW-B or UKW-C
Plugboard:  Yes (10 letter pairs)
Notches:    One per rotor
Key Space:  ~10¹⁶
Country:    Germany 🇩🇪
Years:      1930–1945
Historical Usage:
Standard German Army and Luftwaffe
field cipher from 1930. Used on all
fronts throughout WWII. Daily keys
changed at midnight. Broken by
Polish cryptanalysts 1932–1939,
then by Bletchley Park continuously.
Related Profiles:
[Arthur Scherbius]  [Alan Turing]
[Marian Rejewski]
Related Events:
[Enigma Patent 1918]
[Bombe Operational 1940]" style="rounded=1;arcSize=4;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FAFAFA;strokeColor=#CCCCCC;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1">
